            <run bold='false' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial'>0</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial'>Visualization: </run>
            <run bold='false' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial'>Improved visual aesthetics by adding blue concentration by quarter to easily see the increase in profit by color shade within each year. Hid the Order Date label as it was unnecessary and fit width for better visibility.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial'>Analysis: </run>
            <run bold='false' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial'>This chart provides profit sums at the end of each quarter by category. Because the calculation restarts each year, comparisons by quarter can easily be made. For example, row 1 Audio Equipment jumped in profit by about $70,000 between Q3 and Q4 in 2019, but only by $40,000 between the same quarters in 2020.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </caption>
      </layout-options>
