            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial'>Analysis</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial'>: Visualizing the catogories by Sales vs. Profit in a quadrant chart by average shows which categories produce higher and lower than average sales. While it shows similar information to the Profit by Category Bar Chart, this allows for a broader view of all 47 data points(categories) and explicitly segments into above and below average quadrants. However adding this caption box minimized the chart and it does not appear as useful as in its original form.</run>
