            <run fontname='Arial'>0</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontname='Arial'>Visualization: </run>
            <run fontname='Arial'>Improved visual aesthetics by  changing fonts and color to match workbook theme and sorted in descending order by sales within each region.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontname='Arial'>Analysis: </run>
            <run fontname='Arial'>This chart provides Sales Totals of each state alongside the Fixed_Region LOD to show each state as a component of the regional sales. By sorting, the states with the highest sales are seen first and lowest sales are last within each region. California stands out in the state map, but this fixed LOD column next to state shows that California produces over 50% Sales for the entire West Region.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </caption>
      </layout-options>
      <table>
